[I] A file transfer program

[T] Zsync is a file transfer program. It allows you to download a file from a
[T] remote server, where you have a copy of an older version of the file on
[T] your computer already. zsync downloads only the new parts of the file. It
[T] uses the same algorithm as rsync.

[U] https://zsync.moria.org.uk/

[A] Colin Phipps <cph@moria.org.uk>
